headline: FICO Survey: Brits Call for Stronger Protection as One in Four Report Scam Losses
summary: LONDON, November 18, 2024--(International Fraud Awareness Week) — A new study of 12,000 consumers across 14 countries by global analytics software leader FICO has underscored the need for banks to strike a better balance between customer satisfaction and fraud mitigation as real-time payments (RTP) surge in popularity. In the survey, 26% percent of UK consumers said that they have reported actual or suspected scam losses to their bank.
